    <h1>John's Recipe Book</h1>

    <h2>Contents:</h2>
    <h2 id="recipe1">Recipe #1</h2>

    <ul>
        <li>Time: 30 minutes</li>
        <li>Serves: 4</li>
    </ul>

    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Ingredients</th>
                <th>Quantity</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Ingredient 1 (e.g., Flour)</td>
                <td>1 cup</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Ingredient 2 (e.g., Sugar)</td>
                <td>200g</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Ingredient 3 (e.g., Eggs)</td>
                <td>2</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Ingredient 4 (e.g., Milk)</td>
                <td>1/2 cup</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
    <ol>
        <li>Mix Ingredient 1 and Ingredient 2 in a bowl.</li>
        <li>Add Ingredient 3 and mix well.</li>
        <li>Pour in Ingredient 4 and stir until smooth.</li>
        <li>Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C).</li>
        <li>Pour the batter into a greased baking pan.</li>
        <li>Bake for 20-25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.</li>
    </ol>
<h2 id="recipe2">Recipe #2</h2>

    <ul>
        <li>Time: 45 minutes</li>
        <li>Serves: 6</li>
    </ul>

    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Ingredients</th>
                <th>Quantity</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Ingredient 1 (e.g., Chicken)</td>
                <td>500g</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Ingredient 2 (e.g., Potatoes)</td>
                <td>4 medium-sized</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Ingredient 3 (e.g., Carrots)</td>
                <td>2</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Ingredient 4 (e.g., Olive Oil)</td>
                <td>2 tablespoons</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
    <ol>
        <li>Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).</li>
        <li>Cut the chicken into pieces and season with salt and pepper.</li>
        <li>Chop the potatoes and carrots into bite-sized pieces.</li>
        <li>Place the chicken, potatoes, and carrots on a baking sheet.</li>
        <li>Drizzle olive oil over the ingredients and toss to coat evenly.</li>
        <li>Bake for 30-35 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through and vegetables are tender.</li>
    </ol>


    <h2 id="recipe3">Recipe #3</h2>

    <ul>
        <li>Time: 20 minutes</li>
        <li>Serves: 2</li>
    </ul>

    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Ingredients</th>
                <th>Quantity</th>
            </tr>
